This paper focuses on the problem of modeling relationships between characters in literary novels using a structured prediction approach. The use of linguistic and semantic features to analyze textual content suggests a focus on natural language processing (NLP), which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). Additionally, the use of machine learning techniques to learn relationship sequences from labeled and partially labeled data suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The incorporation of world knowledge to investigate the textual content of narrative suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and semantic web (cs.SD).
